						<h2>Jeffrey Merrihue
							<span>CEO &amp; Co-Founder</span>
						</h2>
						<p>
							Jeffrey began his international marketing career with RJR Nabisco in Spain in 1986. Over the course of
							eight years, he held marketing management positions in Canada, Ecuador, Venezuela, and Italy.
						</p>
						<p>
							Jeffrey moved to Kellogg in 1994, where he served as Marketing director Colombia, Commercial Director
							Mexico / Latin America and finally, Director of European Marketing in Manchester England.
						</p>
						<p>
							In 1998, Jeffrey joined Initiative Media as CEO and European Regional Director and founded Initiative
							Consulting.
						</p>
						<p>
							In 2001 Jeffrey joined Accenture as a partner where he founded Accenture Marketing Sciences and ran the
							group as CEO building a group focused on digital, retail, marketing and media measurement and optimization
							services for the world's most important advertisers.
						</p>
						<p>
							In September 2009, Jeffrey left Accenture to focus full time on MOFILM as Chairman.
						</p>

						<div class="clearBoth"></div>
					</div>
					<div class="member">
						<img src="{$themeimages}/team/team-baker.jpg" class="photo" alt="Andy Baker" style="padding-bottom:140px;"/>

						<h2>Andy Baker
							<span>President &amp; Co-Founder</span>
						</h2>
						<p>
							Andy began MOFILM with Jeffrey after delivering the pioneering Sundance Global Short Film Festival for
							Mobile in collaboration with the GSM Association, which first saw world-famous filmmakers produce
							made-for-mobile films.
						</p>
						<p>
							Andy was previously CEO at grounding breaking digital media company DX3, an early pioneer of downloadable
							music. He has also managed international licensed music and content for service providers globally, with
							a particular interest in mobile and the African market. Andy has held senior management positions at
							Mediawave, WebTV, Energis and Cable &amp; Wireless.
						</p>
						<p>
							Andy served in the Royal Signals within the British Army and is a graduate from Leeds Metropolitan
							University in Communications.
						</p>

						<div class="clearBoth"></div>
					</div>
					<div class="member">
						<img src="{$themeimages}/team/team-jameswalker.jpg" class="photo" alt="James Walker" style="padding-bottom:240px;"/>

						<h2>James Walker
							<span>Managing Director</span>
						</h2>
						<p>
							James Walker is Managing Director at MOFILM. James combines working with some of MOFILM&#8217;s most
							important clients with strategic development initiatives for the company.
						</p>
						<p>
							Prior to MOFILM, James was Chief Strategy and Corporate Development Officer for Nunwood. Under his
							direction, Nunwood won the 2010 MI Award for research agency of the year, and was runner up in the
							2010 Marketing Week research agency of the year awards. James oversaw 2 years of double digit growth
							in tough market conditions, and led Nunwood&#8217;s overseas expansion opening offices in Amsterdam,
							Sydney, Auckland and Los Angeles.
						</p>
						<p>
							James was previously a partner for 7 years at Accenture, the management consultancy, where he was
							President International Accenture Marketing Sciences. James joined Accenture when he and partners
							sold Edge Consulting to Accenture in 2002 to create the kernel of the Accenture Marketing Sciences
							business. AMS grew over 7 years to revenues of $200m, and a team of over 400. Accenture Marketing
							Science&#8217;s growth was a mixture of organic expansion and the acquisition of a number of
							media/digital analytics businesses.
						</p>

						<div class="clearBoth"></div>
					</div>

					<div class="member">
						<img src="{$themeimages}/team/team-smialek.jpg" class="photo" alt="Ken Smialek" />

						<h2>Ken Smialek
							<span>Board Member</span>
